HEADWORD: double-dealer
<hw>dou"ble-deal"er</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>. <def>One who practices double dealing; a deceitful,
trickish person; a person who says one thing and does another.</def>
<rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> double-crosser, betrayer, traitor.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>double-dealing</ent>⟦br⟧
